  <content>
    <chapter line="1">Tudādayo avuddhikā</chapter>
    <hangnum line="2" number="84"></hangnum>
    <gatha1 line="3"> Tuda byathāyaṃ (tu) nuda kkhepaṇe likha lekhaṇe,</gatha1>
    <gathalast line="4">Kuca saṅkocane rica kkharaṇe khaca bandhane;</gathalast>
    <hangnum line="5" number="85"><pageBreak edition="V" number="0.0020" /></hangnum>
    <gatha1 line="6"> Uca sadde samavāye vijī bhayacalesu (ca),</gatha1>
    <gathalast line="7">(Vattate) bhuja koṭille valañjo (tu) valañjane;</gathalast>
    <hangnum line="8" number="86"></hangnum>
    <gatha1 line="9"> Bhaja sevāputhakkāre ruja roge aṭā’ṭane,</gatha1>
    <gathalast line="10">Kuṭacchede (ca) koṭille agā sajjhāyanā’disu;</gathalast>
    <hangnum line="11" number="87"></hangnum>
    <gatha1 line="12"> Puṇo subha kiraye vatta vattane cata yācane,</gatha1>
    <gathalast line="13">Putha pāke pūtibhāve kuthasaṃklesane’(pi ca;)</gathalast>
    <hangnum line="14" number="88"></hangnum>
    <gatha1 line="15"> (Ubho dhātu) putha-patha vitthāre vida jānane,</gatha1>
    <gathalast line="16">Hada uccāra ussagge-cintāyaṃ mida hiṃsane;</gathalast>
    <hangnum line="17" number="89"></hangnum>
    <gatha1 line="18"> Nandha vinandhane thīna-puna saṅghātavācino,</gatha1>
    <gathalast line="19">Kapa acchādane vappa vāraṇe khipa peraṇe;</gathalast>
    <hangnum line="20" number="90"></hangnum>
    <gatha1 line="21"> Supo saye chupo phasse (vattate) capa sāntvane,</gatha1>
    <gathalast line="22">Nabha (dhātu) vihiṃsāyaṃ rumbha uppīḷanādisu;</gathalast>
    <hangnum line="23" number="91"><pageBreak edition="V" number="0.0021" /></hangnum>
    <gatha1 line="24"> Sumbha saṃsumbhane jambha jambhane jubha nicchubhe,</gatha1>
    <gathalast line="25">Ṭhubha niṭṭhubhane camu adane chamu hīḷane;</gathalast>
    <hangnum line="26" number="92"></hangnum>
    <gatha1 line="27"> Jhamu dāhe chamu adane irīya vattane’(pi ca),</gatha1>
    <gathalast line="28">Kira (dhātu) vikiraṇe giro nigiraṇā’disu;</gathalast>
    <hangnum line="29" number="93"></hangnum>
    <gatha1 line="30"> Phura sañcalanādīsu kura saddā’danesu (ca),</gatha1>
    <gathalast line="31">Khuracchede vilikhaṇe ghura bhīme gilā’dane;</gathalast>
    <hangnum line="32" number="94"></hangnum>
    <gatha1 line="33"> Tila snehe cila vāse hila hāve silu’ñchane,</gatha1>
    <gathalast line="34">Bila bhede thūla caye kusacchedana pūraṇe;</gathalast>
    <hangnum line="35" number="95"></hangnum>
    <gatha1 line="36"> Visappavese pharaṇe disā’tisajjanā’disu</gatha1>
    <gatha2 line="37">Phula phasse musa theyye thusa appikirayāya (tu)</gatha2>
    <gathalast line="38">Guḷa mokkhe guḷa parivattanamhi (tudādayo;)</gathalast>
    <paragraph line="39">Hū <pageBreak edition="V" number="0.0022" /> bhuvādayo luttavikaraṇā</paragraph>
    <hangnum line="40" number="96"></hangnum>
    <gatha1 line="41"> Hū-bhū sattāya (mu’ccanti) i ajjhāne gatimhi (ca,)</gatha1>
    <gathalast line="42">Khā-khyā (dvayaṃ) pakathane ji jaye ñā’vabodhane;</gathalast>
    <hangnum line="43" number="97"></hangnum>
    <gatha1 line="44"> Sī-ḷī vehāsagamane ṭhā gatīvinivuttiyaṃ,</gatha1>
    <gathalast line="45">Nī pāpaṇe muna ñāṇe hana hiṃsāgatīsu (’pi)</gathalast>
    <hangnum line="46" number="98"></hangnum>
    <gatha1 line="47"> Pārakkhaṇamhi pā pāne brū vācāyaṃ viyattiyaṃ,</gatha1>
    <gathalast line="48">Bhā dittiyaṃ mā pamāṇe (atho) yā pāpuṇe (siyā;)</gathalast>
    <hangnum line="49" number="99"></hangnum>
    <gatha1 line="50"> (Duvepi) rā-lā ādāne vā gatīgandhanesu (pi,)</gatha1>
    <gathalast line="51">Asa (dhātu) bhuvi (khyāto) si saye sā samatthiye;</gathalast>
